中文；双缝多组角度衍射能量分布验证实验
一、实验目的
验证多组不同角度衍射约束下，能量包交叉排布对明暗纹的重构作用，证实暗纹区域可被完全覆盖，推翻传统光学波动抵消理论。
二、实验装置
平行光发射源
多组不同角度双缝衍射板（设置 3 组及以上不同倾斜角度、间距一致的双缝结构，呈交错排布）
能量接收探测屏
遮光外壳（排除外界杂光干扰）
三、实验步骤
搭建实验光路，将多组角度双缝衍射板置于平行光发射源与能量接收探测屏之间，保证光源垂直入射双缝组。
开启平行光光源，让光线同步穿过所有不同角度的双缝结构，在探测屏上形成纹路分布。
稳定光源输出，观测并记录探测屏上的纹路形态、明暗区域分布状态。
四、传统理论预判
传统光学认为，多组角度衍射仅会形成叠加干涉纹路，暗纹区域依旧存在，是光波相位抵消的结果，不会出现暗区完全覆盖的现象。
五、本理论实验预测
光线穿过多组不同角度双缝后，各组双缝均会产生独立衍射，多方向能量包行进路径全面交叉、相互挤压；
原本单一双缝形成的暗纹区域，会被其他角度衍射的能量包填充覆盖，探测屏上无绝对暗区，仅存在能量包排布疏密不同形成的明暗差异；
明暗纹分布由能量包交叉叠加后的密度决定，而非光波抵消，彻底颠覆传统干涉暗纹成因。
六、实验优势
规避单一光路衍射干扰、观测者效应及介质能量损耗问题，实验变量单一，现象直观，可直接验证能量包排布规律。
English:Verification Experiment on Energy Distribution of Multi-Angle Double-Slit Diffraction
1. Experimental Purpose
To verify the reconstruction effect of cross arrangement of energy packets on bright and dark fringes under multi-angle diffraction constraints, confirm that dark fringe areas can be completely covered, and overturn the traditional optical wave cancellation theory.
2. Experimental Apparatus
Parallel light emitter
Multi-angle double-slit diffraction plates (more than three groups of double-slit structures with the same spacing and different inclination angles, arranged in a staggered form)
Energy receiving detection screen
Light shielding shell (to eliminate interference from external stray light)
3. Experimental Procedures
Build the experimental optical path, place the multi-angle double-slit plates between the parallel light emitter and the energy detection screen, and ensure vertical incidence of light to the slit groups.
Turn on the parallel light source, allow light to pass through all double-slit structures of different angles simultaneously, and form fringe distribution on the detection screen.
Stabilize the light source output, observe and record the fringe morphology and the distribution of bright and dark areas on the screen.
4. Prediction of Traditional Theory
Traditional optics holds that multi-angle diffraction only produces superimposed interference fringes, and dark areas still exist due to wave phase cancellation; complete coverage of dark regions cannot occur.
5. Theoretical Prediction of This System
After light passes through multiple double slits with different angles, each group produces independent diffraction. The traveling paths of multi-directional energy packets fully intersect and squeeze with each other.
The dark areas formed by a single slit will be filled and covered by energy packets diffracted from other angles. There will be no absolute dark region on the detection screen, only brightness differences caused by the dense or sparse arrangement of energy packets.
The distribution of bright and dark fringes is determined by the density of superimposed energy packets, rather than wave cancellation, which fundamentally subverts the traditional explanation of interference dark fringes.
6. Experimental Advantages
This design avoids single optical path interference, observer effect and medium energy loss. With single variable and intuitive phenomena, the experiment can directly verify the arrangement law of energy packets.
